@startuml sequence_scope_registration
!include ../../../design/theme.iuml

title Plugin Scope Registration & Validation

participant "Plugin Process" as Plugin
participant "Manager" as Mgr
participant "Scope Validator" as Val
participant "Config (YAML)" as Cfg
participant "Scope Registry" as Reg
participant "Plugin Registry" as PReg

== Plugin Connects ==

Plugin -> Mgr : RegisterV1 {\n  name: "kafka"\n  requested_scopes: ["write", "keys:kafka:*"]\n  commands: [KAFKA:PRODUCE, KAFKA:CONSUME]\n  hooks: []\n}

Mgr -> Cfg : Get allowed scopes\nfor "kafka"
Cfg --> Mgr : allowed: ["write", "keys:kafka:*"]

Mgr -> Val : Validate(\n  requested=["write", "keys:kafka:*"],\n  allowed=["write", "keys:kafka:*"]\n)

alt All requested scopes are allowed
    Val --> Mgr : OK (granted=["write", "keys:kafka:*"])
    Mgr -> Reg : Store("kafka", granted_scopes)
    Reg --> Mgr : OK
    Mgr -> PReg : Register plugin + commands
    PReg --> Mgr : OK
    Mgr --> Plugin : RegisterAckV1 {\n  accepted: true\n  granted_scopes: ["write", "keys:kafka:*"]\n}
else Requested scope exceeds allowed
    Val --> Mgr : REJECTED ("scope 'admin' not allowed")
    Mgr --> Plugin : RegisterAckV1 {\n  accepted: false\n  reason: "scope 'admin' not in allowed set"\n}
end

== Scope Hierarchy (Implicit Grants) ==

note over Val
  **Scope hierarchy**: admin > write > read

  If config allows "write", plugin also gets "read"
  (write implies read). Explicit "admin" required
  for server-level operations.

  Hook scopes are independent:
  "hook:pre" and "hook:post" must be requested
  and allowed separately.
end note

== No Config = No Scopes ==

note over Cfg
  If no overrides exist for a plugin,
  **default scope = ["read"]** (least privilege).

  Plugins that need more must be explicitly
  configured in gocache.yaml:
    overrides:
      kafka:
        scopes: ["write", "keys:kafka:*"]
end note

@enduml
